      "title": "Sri Lanka shares gain in mid-day trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s shares gained in mid-morning trade on Thursday (28) after slipping for four consecutive sessions, Colombo Stock Exchange data showed as companies release their earnings report for June.",
        "The main All Share Price Index gained 0.93 per cent or 70.86 points to 7,697.55 at 1145 hours.",
        "The most liquid index moved up 1.34 percent or 32.28 points to 2,441.40.",
        "Top gainers were Expolanka, Richard Pieris and Commercial Bank. (Colombo/Jul28/2022)"
      ],
